### Option 1: Inject the MigrationTimestamp into the Logger

```
final class Logger {
    public function __construct(
        private readonly MigrationTimestamp $timestamp,
        private readonly ?string $logfile = null,
        private readonly bool $verbose = false
    ) {}

    public function info(string $msg): void {
        $this->write('INFO', $msg);
    }

    public function verbose(string $msg): void {
        if ($this->verbose) {
            $this->write('VERBOSE', $msg);
        }
    }

    private function write(string $level, string $msg): void {
        $time = $this->timestamp->asString(); // reuse the same timestamp object
        $line = "[$time][$level] $msg" . PHP_EOL;

        if ($this->logfile) {
            file_put_contents($this->logfile, $line, FILE_APPEND);
        }

        echo $line;
    }
}
```

*   Every log line uses the same timestamp instance.
*   No doubling of timezone or formatting logic.
*   You can inject different timestamps for testing if needed.

* * *

