2ÔłŹ‚É£ First fix: isolate env access behind a seam
===============================================

### Step 1: introduce an EnvReader

```
interface EnvReader {
    public function get(string $key): ?string;
}
```

### Production implementation

```
final class PhpEnvReader implements EnvReader {
    public function get(string $key): ?string {
        $value = getenv($key);
        return $value === false ? null : $value;
    }
}
```

* * *

3ÔłŹ‚É£ Make config creation testable
=================================

```
final class DomainEnvironmentFactory {

    public function __construct(
        private EnvReader $env
    ) {}

    public function create(): DomainEnvironment {
        $envName = $this->env->get('WP_ENV') ?? 'local';

        return match ($envName) {
            'local'   => require __DIR__ . '/env/local.php',
            'staging' => require __DIR__ . '/env/staging.php',
            'live'    => require __DIR__ . '/env/live.php',
            default   => throw new InvalidArgumentException("Unknown env: $envName"),
        };
    }
}
```

Now **no globals inside your logic**.

* * *

4ÔłŹ‚É£ Unit-testing this (clean & boring ūüėĄ)
=========================================

### Fake EnvReader for tests

```
final class FakeEnvReader implements EnvReader {

    public function __construct(
        private array $vars
    ) {}

    public function get(string $key): ?string {
        return $this->vars[$key] ?? null;
    }
}
```

* * *

### PHPUnit test

