* * *

### 1ÔłŹ‚É£ Extend your runner to detect DB commands

You can check if the command is DB-related (`db export`, `search-replace`, etc.) and automatically append `--skip-ssl`:

```
class DockerComposeRunner implements CommandRunner {

    public function __construct(
        private CommandExecutor $executor,
        private DockerComposeContext $docker,
        private string $service = 'wpcli',
        public ?MigrationLogger $logger = null,
    ) {
        $this->logger = $logger ?? new NullLogger();
    }

    public function build_command(WpCliCommand $command): string {
        $args = $command->args;

        // Automatically add --skip-ssl if this is a DB command
        if ($this->is_db_command($args)) {
            if (!in_array('--skip-ssl', $args, true)) {
                $args[] = '--skip-ssl';
            }
        }

        $command_args = implode(' ', array_map('escapeshellarg', $args));

        $compose_prefix = DockerComposeCommandBuilder::build_prefix($this->docker);

        return sprintf(
            '%s run --rm %s %s',
            $compose_prefix,
            escapeshellarg($this->service),
            $command_args
        );
    }

    private function is_db_command(array $args): bool {
        // WP-CLI commands that require DB connection
        $db_commands = ['db', 'search-replace'];
        return isset($args[0]) && in_array($args[0], $db_commands, true);
    }

    public function run(WpCliCommand $command): CommandResult {
        $cmd = $this->build_command($command);
        $this->logger->info("Running: $cmd");
        return $this->executor->execute($cmd);
    }
}
```

* * *

### 2ÔłŹ‚É£ Why this works

*   Any DB command (`db export`, `search-replace`, `db import`) automatically gets `--skip-ssl`.
*   Non-DB commands (`db size`, `cli info`, `plugin list`) are unaffected, so you won‚Äôt get errors.
*   Your `WpCliCommandBuilder` doesn‚Äôt need to worry about SSL anymore ‚ÄĒ the runner handles it globally.

* * *

