Ah ‚ÄĒ now we‚Äôre talking about a **debug/logging helper** for `MigrationState`. The goal of `dump()` is to give you a **human-readable snapshot** of all `StateDelta` entries in the current migration run, for inspection or logging.

Here‚Äôs a clean way to do it:

```
final class MigrationState
{
    /** @var StateDelta[] */
    private array $deltas = [];

    public function set(string $key, mixed $value): void
    {
        $this->deltas[$key] = $value;
    }

    public function get(string $key, mixed $default = null): mixed
    {
        return $this->deltas[$key] ?? $default;
    }

    /**
     * Return a formatted dump of the current state for debugging/logging.
     */
    public function dump(): string
    {
        if (empty($this->deltas)) {
            return "[MigrationState] (empty)";
        }

        $lines = ["[MigrationState] Current deltas:"];
        foreach ($this->deltas as $key => $value) {
            // Convert arrays/objects to JSON for readability
            if (is_array($value) || is_object($value)) {
                $valStr = json_encode($value, JSON_PRETTY_PRINT);
            } else {
                $valStr = (string) $value;
            }

            $lines[] = sprintf("  %s: %s", $key, $valStr);
        }

        return implode(PHP_EOL, $lines);
    }
}
```

