*   `MysqlCommand` carries everything the runner needs: `args`, `env`, `description`.
*   Runner just builds the Docker command and executes it.
*   No temporary CNF file needed.
*   Visibility is clean: only `$env` is public so runner can use it, everything else is encapsulated.

