Yep ‚ÄĒ **this is the missing piece**. Right now WordPress is assuming the default:

*   `WP_CONTENT_DIR = ABSPATH . 'wp-content'` ‚Üí `/var/www/html/wp-content`
*   so WP-CLI lists default themes/plugins (because it looks in `/var/www/html/wp-content`)
*   while _your_ real content is in `/antoniuskoor/wordpress/wp-content`

So you need to **define WP\_CONTENT\_DIR and WP\_CONTENT\_URL before `wp-settings.php`**.

Add this block just after you set `WP_HOME/WP_SITEURL` (or anywhere before the final `require_once ABSPATH . '/wp-settings.php';`).

Fix: set custom wp-content location
-----------------------------------

```
// ----------------------------------------------------
// Content directory (non-standard layout)
// ----------------------------------------------------

// Physical path to wp-content (host-mounted into container)
define('WP_CONTENT_DIR', PROJECT_ROOT . '/wp-content');

// URL path to wp-content (must match how Apache serves it)
if (!defined('WP_CONTENT_URL')) {
    // Prefer explicit env, fall back to WP_HOME
    $base = getenv('WP_HOME') ?: (defined('WP_HOME') ? WP_HOME : '');
    if ($base) {
        define('WP_CONTENT_URL', rtrim($base, '/') . '/wp-content');
    } else {
        // Last resort: relative URL
        define('WP_CONTENT_URL', '/wp-content');
    }
}
```

### Important note about _paths_

In your container:

*   `PROJECT_ROOT` is `/var/www/html` (because wp-config.php is mounted there)
*   but your real wp-content is **NOT** `/var/www/html/wp-content`
*   it‚Äôs `/antoniuskoor/wordpress/wp-content`

So the line:

```
define('WP_CONTENT_DIR', PROJECT_ROOT . '/wp-content');
```

is only correct **if** you also mount `.../wordpress/wp-content` to `/var/www/html/wp-content`.

Right now you _don‚Äôt_.

### The cleanest option (no code changes later)

Add one volume mapping so WordPress sees wp-content where it expects it:

```
- /projects/antoniuskoor/wordpress/wp-content:/var/www/html/wp-content
```

Then you can keep:

```
define('WP_CONTENT_DIR', PROJECT_ROOT . '/wp-content');
```

### If you prefer _no extra volume mapping_

Then set WP\_CONTENT\_DIR to the real location:

```
define('WP_CONTENT_DIR', '/antoniuskoor/wordpress/wp-content');
```

(That‚Äôs valid, but it hardcodes the container path.)

* * *

