### Artifact base class: minimal patch

```
abstract class Artifact
{
    // ‚Ä¶ existing ctor, fields, etc ‚Ä¶

    /**
     * Optional: subclasses can throw if something is missing (file not found, not readable, etc)
     */
    protected function validate(): void
    {
        // default: no validation
    }

    /**
     * Optional: subclasses can return a more realistic dry-run result.
     */
    protected function simulate_result(): CommandResult
    {
        return new CommandResult(
            command: '[SIMULATED] ' . $this->type->name,
            executed: false,
            exitcode: 0,
            stdout: '',
            stderr: '',
        );
    }

    final public function run(): CommandResult
    {
        if (! $this->runner) {
            throw new \RuntimeException("No Runner assigned to artifact: {$this->type->name}");
        }

        // 1) Always validate (even in dry-run)
        $this->validate();

        // 2) Dry-run behavior
        if ($this->context->dry_run()) {
            // If you have per-artifact policy, gate it here.
            // Example:
            // if ($this->type->dry_run_policy() === DryRunPolicy::SKIP_EXECUTION) {
            //     return $this->simulate_result();
            // }

            // If your dry-run means "never execute external commands":
            return $this->simulate_result();
        }

        // 3) Real execution
        $result = $this->runner->run_operation($this->operation());

        // 4) Centralized error tracking + aborts
        // (You said you want one function for errors+warnings: do it here.)
        $this->context->state()->track_result(
            artifact: $this->type,
            result: $result
        );

        // If you want abort-on-error:
        if (! $result->succeeded()) {
            throw new \RuntimeException("Artifact failed: {$this->type->name}");
        }

        return $result;
    }

    abstract public function state_delta(CommandResult $result): StateDelta|array;
}
```

