public function state_delta(CommandResult $result): array
{
    $count = $this->parse_result($result->stdout);

    $deltas = [];
    $deltas[] = new StateDelta(StateDeltaType::SEARCH_REPLACE, [
        'phase'        => 'plan',
        'base_name'    => $this->filename_suffix(),
        // I would NOT put replacements in plan; it‚Äôs a result.
    ]);

    $message = "Search-replace"
        . ($result->executed ? ': ' : ' (simulated): ')
        . $count . ' replacements detected';
    $this->logger->info($message);

    $payload = [
        'phase'        => 'result',
        'executed'     => $result->executed,
        'replacements' => $count,
    ];

    // Only include file/size if it was actually produced
    if ($result->executed) {
        $payload['export_file'] = $this->target_file;
        $payload['size'] = $this->human_filesize($this->target_file);
    }

    $deltas[] = new StateDelta(StateDeltaType::SEARCH_REPLACE, $payload);

    return $deltas;
}
```

This makes dry-run consistent across artifacts: **plan + result always**, and the result tells you whether it happened.

